The paper proposes an automatic approach and tool for extracting specifications from web API documentation pages using machine learning techniques. This involves crawling documentation pages, identifying base URLs, path templates, and HTTP methods. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. However, the use of machine learning techniques for information retrieval and natural language processing suggests that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Deep Learning (cs.DL), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
